The paper deals with deep learning-based super-resolution (SR) applications, which are typically categorized under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel network utilizing maxout units (MU) and investigates their effects on SR applications. This suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and multimedia (cs.MM).
